This memorandum, issued by President Barack Obama on January 30, 2009, establishes the White House Task Force on Middle-Class Working Families. The task force is created to focus on raising the living standards of middle-class working families in the United States. The Vice President serves as the Chair of the Task Force, and it consists of various executive branch departments, agencies, and offices such as the Department of Commerce, Department of Labor, Department of Health and Human Services, and others. The Task Force's mission is to work with these departments and agencies to propose reforms, develop legislative and policy proposals, and provide recommendations on expanding education and training opportunities, improving work and family balance, restoring labor standards, protecting incomes and retirement security of middle-class working families. The Task Force is also required to conduct outreach with various stakeholders and engage in transparency and reporting by posting submissions and annual reports on the internet. The memorandum emphasizes that the implementation of this directive should be consistent with applicable law and subject to the availability of appropriations.